=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Hunting Spots..</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">What are the tricks for root/doting anyway? Use root/install/paralyzing earth? Whenever I do that, the roots always seem to break from the intial damage of a dot, no matter which root I use too.. gets frustrating sometimes <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Which &quot;root&quot; type spell is the best to use for a situation like Charsis?  Or is it easier to skip using ebolt and plague and just use BoD/splurt/ignite blood/asystole or whatever has no initial damage?<br>
