</font><font face="Arial" size="2">T</font><font face="Arial" size="1">`VYL</font></p><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxveeroflanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XveerOfLanys</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>n00b!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>10/26/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:11:29 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Hunting Spots..</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The giant fortress was great around lvl 51-53 but when you hit lvl 54-55 most of them become green.  Skyfire is ok (great for a outside area).  You can fear kite safely at the BW entrance.  I started soloing there at lvl 51 since you get Splurt and EB.  If both DOTs stick the first time you can take down a Wurm, Wyvern, Chroma or drakes with less then 2 bubs of mana.  Here's how I do it:<br>
<br>
1) Pull with Splurt<br>
2) Send pet<br>
3) Fear<br>
4) Darkness (use Dooming)<br>
5) EB (only use with Mature and Old)<br>
6) Bond<br>
7) Med and Fear when necessary<br>
<br>
Lich was up all the time and when you back with Full Mana the pet is full and I was at 80% hp.  With this technique you should have very short downtime.<br>
<br>
